description: Take list of odd numbers, move left digit of each term to end of previous term.
links: Reinhard Zumkeller, Table of n, a(n) for n = 0..10000
prog: (Haskell)a032764 n = a032764_list !! na032764_list = 1 : map read (zipWith (++) vs (tail us)) :: [Integer]   where (us,vs) = unzip $ map ((splitAt 1) . show) [1, 3 ..]-- _Reinhard Zumkeller_, Oct 10 2013
author: _Patrick De Geest_, May 15 1998
